### Order Service API Testing
### Make sure to:
### 1. Start Hardhat node: npm run hardhat:node
### 2. Deploy contracts: npm run hardhat:deploy
### 3. Seed data: npx hardhat run scripts/seed-data.js --network localhost
### 4. Start service: npm run service:start

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3003/api/v1

### 1. Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### 2. Get All Listings
GET {{baseUrl}}/listings

### 3. Get Specific Listing
GET {{baseUrl}}/listings/lst_001_hoodie

### 4. Create Order (without payment)
POST {{baseUrl}}/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "listingId": "lst_001_hoodie",
  "quantity": 2,
  "buyerAddress": "0xf39Fd6e51aad88F6F4ce6aB8827279cffFb92266"
}

### 5. Get All Orders
GET {{baseUrl}}/orders

### 6. Get Specific Order (replace with actual orderId from step 4)
GET {{baseUrl}}/orders/ord_1234567890_abcd1234

### 7. Pay for Order (replace with actual orderId from step 4)
POST {{baseUrl}}/orders/ord_1234567890_abcd1234/pay
Content-Type: application/json

### 8. Update Order Status to Shipped
PUT {{baseUrl}}/orders/ord_1234567890_abcd1234/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "shipped",
  "notes": "Shipped via DHL, tracking: DHL123456789"
}

### 9. Confirm Delivery and Release Escrow
POST {{baseUrl}}/orders/ord_1234567890_abcd1234/confirm-delivery
Content-Type: application/json

### 10. Get Escrow by Order ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/escrow/order/ord_1234567890_abcd1234

### 11. Cancel Order (use a new order that hasn't been paid)
POST {{baseUrl}}/orders/ord_1234567890_abcd1234/cancel
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "reason": "Changed my mind"
}

### 12. Filter Orders by Buyer
GET {{baseUrl}}/orders?buyer=0xf39Fd6e51aad88F6F4ce6aB8827279cffFb92266

### 13. Filter Orders by Status
GET {{baseUrl}}/orders?status=paid

